Place in a bowl the self-raising flour, baking powder, eggs and milk.  Mix together to form a thick batter.Add the icing sugar and blueberries.Melt the butter in a frying pan and ladle in the blueberry pancake mix a ladleful at a time.  Cook the pancakes until golden brown, on both sides.Stack the blueberry pancakes and leave to one side.For the blueberry sauce, in a pan add the red wine with the sugar, cloves, mixed spice and the blueberries.Simmer for four minutes, and take off the heat.Put the sauce through a sieve and remove the cloves.To serve, place the stack of pancakes in the middle of the plate and drizzle with the blueberry sauce.